    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Don't Ask, Don't Translate,'' by Stephen Benjamin (Op-Ed, June 8):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Don't Ask, Don't Translate,'' by Stephen Benjamin (Op-Ed, June 8):</p>
        <p>We pay our brave soldiers a grave insult by sending them into lethal conditions day after day and then assuming that they are not mature enough to overcome the personal differences of their peers.</p>
        <p>Our military lacks translators and recruits -- not a sense of dignity. And a policy that proudly welcomes the service of all its members could never take that away.</p>
        <p>Julia Collins  Stratford, Conn., June 8, 2007</p>
      </block>
